The paper deals with problems related to clustering and distance selection on finite metric spaces, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of graph shortest path metrics and high-dimensional Euclidean metrics suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and complexity analysis, which are relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of information theory techniques, which may indicate a connection to the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
